  "text": "The Envoy v1.31.2 codebase contains comprehensive implementation of dual xDS v2 and v3 API handling for the Aggregated Discovery Service (ADS) and related xDS protocols. The v2 to v3 migration is managed through proto versioning annotations and dual-stream support architecture.\n\n## Proto Definitions\n\nThe proto files define both v2 and v3 APIs with explicit versioning annotations:\n\n1. **v2 Discovery API** (`api/envoy/api/v2/discovery.proto`): Defines `DiscoveryRequest` and `DiscoveryResponse` messages for v2 API clients.\n\n2. **v3 Discovery API** (`api/envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto`): Contains updated `DiscoveryRequest`/`DiscoveryResponse` with new fields like `resource_locators` and includes versioning annotations: `option (udpa.annotations.versioning).previous_message_type = \"envoy.api.v2.DiscoveryRequest\"` to track the migration path.\n\n3. **v2 ADS Service** (`api/envoy/service/discovery/v2/ads.proto`): Defines `AggregatedDiscoveryService` using v2 request/response types (`api.v2.DiscoveryRequest`, `api.v2.DiscoveryResponse`, `api.v2.DeltaDiscoveryRequest`, `api.v2.DeltaDiscoveryResponse`).\n\n4. **v3 ADS Service** (`api/envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads.proto`): Defines updated `AggregatedDiscoveryService` using v3 types, includes versioning annotation `option (udpa.annotations.versioning).previous_message_type = \"envoy.service.discovery.v2.AdsDummy\"`.\n\n## C++ Implementation - ADS gRPC Server\n\nThe C++ codebase implements the dual-version subscription handling through template-based polymorphism and type-specific implementations:\n\n### Primary ADS Implementations\n\n1. **GrpcMuxImpl** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h` and `.cc`): \n   - Main implementation of the ADS gRPC server\n   - Handles state-of-the-world (SotW) protocol\n   - Uses v3 `DiscoveryRequest`/`DiscoveryResponse` from `envoy::service::discovery::v3`\n   - Manages subscription state via `ApiState` struct tracking `envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest` objects\n   - Key method: `handleDiscoveryResponse()` processes responses and `onDiscoveryResponse()` handles stream callbacks\n\n2. **NewGrpcMuxImpl** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h` and `.cc`):\n   - Alternative delta-only ADS implementation\n   - Inherits from `GrpcStreamCallbacks<envoy::service::discovery::v3::DeltaDiscoveryResponse>`\n   - Manages delta protocol subscriptions with `DeltaSubscriptionState`\n   - Implements `onDiscoveryResponse()` for delta discovery responses\n\n### Templated Generic ADS Implementation\n\n3. **xds_mux::GrpcMuxImpl** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h` and `.cc`):\n   - Templated implementation: `template <class S, class F, class RQ, class RS>`\n   - Supports both SotW and Delta protocols through subscription state factories\n   - Parameterized by request and response types (RQ, RS) - currently instantiated with v3 types\n   - Method `genericHandleResponse()` provides polymorphic response handling\n   - Manages subscriptions map of type `absl::flat_hash_map<std::string, std::unique_ptr<S>>`\n\n### Subscription State Management\n\n4. **SotwSubscriptionState** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h` and `.cc`):\n   - Extends `BaseSubscriptionState<envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryResponse, envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest>`\n   - Implements state-of-the-world protocol logic\n   - Tracks `last_good_version_info_` and `last_good_nonce_` for v3 responses\n\n5. **DeltaSubscriptionState** (in both `/source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/` and `/source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/`):\n   - Extends `BaseSubscriptionState` with v3 delta discovery types\n   - Implements delta discovery protocol logic with resource state tracking\n   - Returns `envoy::service::discovery::v3::DeltaDiscoveryRequest` from `getNextRequestInternal()`\n\n### Protocol Stream Handling\n\n6. **GrpcMuxFailover** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_failover.h`):\n   - Template class: `template <class RequestType, class ResponseType>`\n   - Supports both SotW (v3 `DiscoveryRequest`/`DiscoveryResponse`) and Delta-xDS (v3 `DeltaDiscoveryRequest`/`DeltaDiscoveryResponse`)\n   - Implements primary/failover stream arbitration with identical request/response types\n   - Comments indicate capability to handle both protocol variants\n\n7. **GrpcStream** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream.h`):\n   - Template class: `template <class RequestProto, class ResponseProto>`\n   - Generic gRPC stream implementation for xDS\n   - Currently used with v3 proto types\n   - Method `onReceiveMessage()` provides polymorphic message handling\n\n## Proto Type Version Resolution\n\n8. **type_to_endpoint** (`source/common/config/type_to_endpoint.h` and `.cc`):\n   - Maps resource type URLs to appropriate gRPC service methods\n   - Explicitly enumerates v3 services only: `envoy.service.route.v3.RouteDiscoveryService`, etc.\n   - Functions `sotwGrpcMethod()`, `deltaGrpcMethod()`, `restMethod()` look up versioned service methods\n   - Comment at line 47: \"service methods (versioned by transport_api_version)\"\n   - Builds `TypeUrlToV3ServiceMap` mapping type URLs to `V3Service` (SotW and Delta methods)\n\n## API Version Validation\n\n9. **utility.h** (`source/common/config/utility.h`):\n   - Contains `checkTransportVersion()` template method for validating `transport_api_version`\n   - Validates against `envoy::config::core::v3::ApiVersion` enum\n   - Explicit deprecation message: \"V2 xDS transport protocol version is deprecated in [config]. The v2 xDS major version has been removed and is no longer supported.\"\n   - Currently only accepts `ApiVersion::AUTO` and `ApiVersion::V3`\n\n10. **api_version.h** (`source/common/config/api_version.h`):\n    - Provides API version macro: `API_NO_BOOST(x)` to prevent version boosting\n    - Prevents automatic API version updates for specific proto definitions\n\n## Bootstrap Configuration Migration Tool\n\n11. **bootstrap2pb** (`tools/bootstrap2pb.cc`):\n    - Utility tool for converting bootstrap configuration between formats\n    - Includes v2 bootstrap proto: `#include \"envoy/config/bootstrap/v2/bootstrap.pb.h\"`\n    - Demonstrates historical v2 to v3 migration path\n    - Loads v2 bootstrap and outputs proto text format\n\n## Field Migration Details\n\nKey field differences between v2 and v3 DiscoveryRequest:\n- v2: Uses `core.Node` reference\n- v3: Uses `config.core.v3.Node` reference\n- v3 adds: `repeated ResourceLocator resource_locators` field (field 7)\n- Both maintain: `string version_info`, `repeated string resource_names`, `string type_url`, `string response_nonce`, `google.rpc.Status error_detail`\n\n## Dual-Version Architecture Summary\n\nThe implementation achieves dual v2/v3 support through:\n\n1. **Proto-level compatibility**: Both v2 and v3 proto files exist with versioning annotations linking them\n2. **Template-based polymorphism**: Classes like `GrpcMuxFailover` and `GrpcStream` use templates to support different request/response type pairs\n3. **Subscription state abstraction**: `BaseSubscriptionState` and its subclasses handle both protocol variants (SotW and Delta)\n4. **Type mapping abstraction**: `type_to_endpoint.cc` provides version-agnostic service method lookup\n5. **Version validation**: `checkTransportVersion()` ensures proper API version negotiation\n\nNote: In v1.31.2, v2 is deprecated but the proto definitions remain for backward compatibility and legacy tool support. The C++ runtime implementation exclusively uses v3 types, with the architecture designed to support protocol-level differences (SotW vs Delta) rather than API version differences."
